RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 1 1M Turf CR: 80. Allowance Purse 28000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR MINNESOTA BRED WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the Turf, it will be ru n at a distance of 1 Mile on the main track.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ANN ALEE was sent to the front to set the pace on the inside while clear, then remained clear to the wire while being kept to left handed crop to the sixteenth pole and then was ridden out the final hundred yards to prove much the best. HONEY BELLA chased the winner two wide throughout, failed to gain on that rival while being clearly second best. CHECKCASHINGCONNIE was rated along the inside, then was shuffled back and angled out by the quarter pole, came five wide into the lane and was along for the show award. CALY BALI broke in a tangle at the start, then raced two wide and came four wide into the lane and had no rally, out-kicked for the show award. MIDNIGHT LANE was settled early four to three wide and weakened. DELUSIONAL DREAM was settled back and three wide on the backstretch and failed to respond.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 2 5F Turf CR: 92. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 28000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, TRIAL OR STATE BRED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $8,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $16,000. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 16 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $25,000. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the Turf, it will be run at adi stance of 5 Furlongs on the main track.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MACHO ROCCO pressed the early pace to the inside of LOVE MY JIMMY and racing in the two path, then rated off the front runner and shifted out and made a four wide bid off the turn, went on even terms by the furlong marker and then drew clear to prove best, driving. LOVE MY JIMMY was away alertly to set the pace while racing off the rail, shook clear on the turn, then was headed by the furlong marker and could not go with the winner while staying on for the place. HURTS SO GOOD was well placed early on the inside but lacked the needed stretch bid, held show award. MARVELOUS THUNDER chased the early pace three to two wide, then dropped to the inside in the lane and had no kick, missed show award. CHANNEL WON was settled two to three wide and then showed some late interest while racing evenly. MISTER BANJOMAN tracked the pace four wide, came five wide into the lane and weakened. SAMURAI MIKE was settled early, three wide on the turn and had no rally. SAINT CHARLES raced on the inside and checked by the three eighths marker and dropped back. HAP HOT failed to respond.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 3 5F Turf CR: 64. Maiden Claiming Purse 10500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SMART LEAH was well placed early towards the inside, made a two wide bid off the turn and drew clear, then remained clear to prove best, driving. SHEZA REAL DEAL was allowed to settle early, saved ground on the turn and made a bid off the turn but flattened out, held place award. TAMMY MACHO was settled early, three wide on the turn and rallied. DANZINGWITHROYALTY was off a step slow, then saved ground and finished well late. GRACEFUL MOON chased the pace three wide and had no kick, even effort. ROLL GYPSY ROLL was bumped at the start, settled back, swung out four wide leaving the turn, then was blocked by the furlong marker, angled out to the outside and had a late kick. KARATS KOUNT was away alertly to set the early pace while off the inside, then bolted on the turn and fell back. TATUM'S JOURNEY stalked the pace four wide, then made a three wide bid to inherit the lead when the front runner bolted, then weakened in the drive. DR Z'S ELSA was settled early on the outside, made a wide move on the turn and came wide into the lane but flattened out. IT'S ME was fractious in the gate, then failed to menace. MAJESTIC CINEMA tracked the pace three wide and stopped. There was about an hour delay while they worked on the main track, after the riders deemed the sloppy dirt surface not safe the race was moved to the yielding turf race.
